<div><h3>EN 207 - Climate Change, Energy and Development </h3>  <hr><p class="MsoNormal"><span>This course explores the challenges associated with climate change, energy and development from multiple perspectives, disciplines and scales. The course explores the evolving science of climate change, the uneven distribution of climate change impacts throughout the world, the challenges of integrating science into effective climate policy, energy technology innovation, technologies and policies for climate change mitigation and climate change adaptation, and the associated conflicts between and diversity among challenges of developed and developing countries. This course is designed for graduate students and advanced undergraduates.</span><br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Fall or Spring<br><br></div>		</td>
